<font color="#FF0000">VIETNAM - AFTER EFFECTS</font><br>
<tt>Sun Jan 26 16:39:41 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I was a twenty year soldier.  I spend two plus tours in VietNam, one as an advisor.  I have seen both sides of the war.  The after effects of a village not giving their all to the VC, and not playing the game with the ARVIN's (good guys?).  The oldest of the old VietNamese knew nothing but war and fighting, regardless of the reason, it was still taking and killing.  They did it with bullets and knifes, we (Americans) today do it with taxes, political connections and &quot;I can get away with it because I's powerful&quot; attitudes. So which is worse, physically dead or moraly dead?<br><br>
I did hang in there and server my time,<br>
Now I pay with soul and mind.
